The paper proposes new methods for enhancing the performance of genetic algorithms, which are commonly used in optimization problems. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes new crossover and mutation operators, which are commonly used in genetic algorithms, indicating a possible fit with cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The experiments conducted on Travelling Salesman Problems (TSP) suggest a possible fit with cs.OH (Operations Research, Mathematical Programming) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
